  "text": "However, in the presence of coronary artery disease, the Hb threshold may increase. In animal models it has been reported that Hb threshold may be at a level of 7-7.5 g/dL in the presence of coronary artery stenosis with limited tolerance to isovolemic hemodilution [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
